OL,3,CWeather warning in place as strong
OL,4,Cwinds cause disruption
OL,6,FIn a statement the Met Office said:
OL,7,F"Strong winds are expected during
OL,8,FThursday associated with an active
OL,9,Fweather front moving southeastwards
OL,10,Facross the UK.
OL,12,F"Gusts of 50-55 mph are expected
OL,13,Fwidely, with some coastal locations
OL,14,Fand areas downwind of high ground
OL,15,Fseeing gusts of 60 mph or even 70 mph
OL,16,Fin a few places.
OL,18,F"Winds will ease from the north
OL,19,Fthrough the day."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/4
